            <h1>High-Risk AI Systems under EU AI Act</h1>
            <p>Under Article 6 of the EU AI Act, AI systems intended to be used as a safety component of the following products are automatically considered high risk:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Machinery - Covers various mechanical devices and installations, such as industrial machines.</li>
                <li>Toys - Pertains to consumer products designed for children's play.</li>
                <li>Recreational Craft and Personal Watercraft - Includes boats, yachts, jet skis, and similar water vehicles.</li>
                <li>Lifts and Safety Components for Lifts - Involves elevators and their critical safety parts.</li>
                <li>Equipment for Potentially Explosive Atmospheres - Refers to devices used in environments where explosive conditions may exist.</li>
                <li>Radio Equipment - Encompasses devices that emit or receive radio waves for communication.</li>
                <li>Pressure Equipment - Covers vessels, piping, safety valves, and other components designed to hold or transport pressurized substances.</li>
                <li>Cableway Installations - Includes cable cars, ski lifts, and similar transport systems used primarily in mountainous areas.</li>
                <li>Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) - Encompasses items like helmets, gloves, and protective clothing.</li>
                <li>Appliances Burning Gaseous Fuels - Refers to gas-operated devices such as heaters and stoves.</li>
                <li>Medical Devices - Includes a broad range of instruments, machines, and implants used in healthcare.</li>
                <li>In Vitro Diagnostic Medical Devices - Pertains to devices used to perform tests on samples outside a living organism, such as blood tests.</li>
                <li>Civil Aviation Security - Relates to the security measures and equipment used in civil aviation.</li>
                <li>Two- or Three-Wheel Vehicles and Quadricycles - Covers motorcycles, scooters, and similar small motor vehicles.</li>
                <li>Agricultural and Forestry Vehicles - Includes tractors, harvesters, and other heavy machinery used in farming and forestry.</li>
                <li>Marine Equipment - Encompasses items used on ships, such as safety gear and navigation devices.</li>
                <li>Rail System Interoperability - Relates to the compatibility of rail infrastructure, vehicles, and systems across the EU.</li>
                <li>Motor Vehicles and Trailers - Covers cars, trucks, trailers, and all related components and systems.</li>
                <li>General Safety of Motor Vehicles - Focuses on the overall safety requirements for motor vehicles and their occupants.</li>
                <li>Aircraft and Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs) - Includes manned aircraft, drones, and related parts and equipment.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For a full list and more details, see Annex II of the EU AI Act.</p>
